addInvestor(address,uint256,uint256,uint.details: Add an investor to the vesting contract

params._cliff: : cliff as seconds after start time
params._duration: : duration as seconds after start time
params._start: : start time of the vesting period

amount(address).details: Getter for the amount of tokens to vest

cliff(address).details: Getter for the cliff of the vesting period

params._tokenToVest: : address of the token to vest

duration(address).details: Getter for the duration of the vesting period

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

releasable(address).details: Getter for the amount of releasable token.

release(address).details: Release the native token (token) that have already vested.

params.investor: The address of the investor Emits a {tokenReleased} event.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

start(address).details: Getter for the start time of the vesting period

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

vestedAmount(uint64,address).details: Calculates the amount of token that has already vested. Default implementation is a linear vesting curve.

params.timestamp: The timestamp at which the vested amount is calculated
